what it is: a big array in roblox's memory that maps normal opcodes to the shuffled ones roblox uses

what its used for: roblox shufles their opcodes so u cant just compile bytecode normally and feed it in u use this
table to convert ur opcodes to match what roblox expects so the VM actually accepts ur scripts

how u use it: when compiling u take each opcode do some math on it
then look it up in the table to get the shuffled version if this address is wrong or outdated ur scripts just wont execute
